                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d745">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War, 1939/17596</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Chinese Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="79" xml:id="d745fn1">Handed to the Under Secretary of State by the
                        Chinese Ambassador on August 22, 1941.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1941-08-22">undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Translation of a telegram to Ambassador Hu Shih from
                        Foreign Minister Quo Tai-chi, Chungking, August</hi> 20, 1941</p>
                <p>… The Generalissimo and public opinion in general are greatly disappointed by the
                    apparent fact that, while the relation between the Soviet Union and the
                    Anglo-Saxon Powers has become closer, China, which has been fighting the first
                    battles against aggression, now appears to be entirely left out of the councils
                    of the “Inner Circle.” We fully realize that the purpose of the coming Moscow
                    Conference is to discuss ways and means to aid Russia and to combat German
                    aggression, but we cannot help feeling that something should be done towards
                    China, preferably in the form of an invitation to China to send delegates to
                    participate in the Conference so as to demonstrate to the outside world the
                    unity of the anti-aggression. …<note n="79a" xml:id="d745fn2">Omissions
                        indicated in the original.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
